A man who allegedly raped a shop owner and murdered his brother in Prestbury, Pietermaritzburg, has handed himself over to the police. According to police, the man, who is around 30 years old, handed himself to the Prestbury Police Station on Monday night. It is alleged that he broke into the shop where the brother was sleeping and stabbed him over 20 times on Saturday just after 10pm. The following day, when the sister who owned the shop came to collect her charger she was allegedly grabbed by the man and raped repeatedly. The sister was kept the whole day in the shop and when she did not return home, her husband went to the shop to look for her. When he got to the shop, he found the man raping his wife and his brother-in-law was lying in a pool of blood. The unknown man fled the scene.